---
import TechnologyLayout from '../../layouts/TechnologyLayout.astro';
import TextSection from '../../components/content/TextSection.astro';
import SectionWrapper from '../../components/ui/SectionWrapper.astro';
import WhenToChoose from '../../components/content/WhenToChoose.astro';
import HowWeUseIt from '../../components/content/HowWeUseIt.astro';
---

<TechnologyLayout
  title="Metabase | Nimzo Data"
  description="Metabase implementation on BigQuery — dashboards, governed metrics, Metabot AI, and flexible deployment options."
  toolName="Metabase"
  toolCategory="Business Intelligence"
  heroPositioning="Metabase is self-service BI for teams that want broad access, a real AI assistant, and the flexibility to self-host — without enterprise-tier spend."
>
  <TextSection title="What It Is" bg="white">
    <p>Metabase is approachable BI with a full dashboarding, metric, and question-building surface. Business users explore data through a visual interface; analysts build reusable Models and Metrics that enforce consistent definitions; power users drop into SQL when they need it. Metabot — Metabase's AI assistant, open-sourced in version 60 — generates charts, writes SQL, analyzes results, and answers questions in natural language.</p>
  </TextSection>

  <TextSection title="Why We Chose It" bg="white">
    <p>Metabase is the pragmatic middle of the BI market. It's cheaper than Looker, broader than Steep, and more flexible than Lightdash — you can run it fully self-hosted on Cloud Run, use Metabase Cloud, or start free on the Community Edition. The semantic layer (Models + Metrics + Data Studio) matured fast in 2025–2026, and Metabot's AI features — including self-hosted AI with your own Anthropic API key — make it a strong option for AI-powered BI without the cloud-only lock-in of Looker.</p>
  </TextSection>

  <SectionWrapper bg="white" py="lg">
    <HowWeUseIt
      title="How We Use It"
      items={[
        "Stand up Metabase — Metabase Cloud for managed, or self-hosted on Cloud Run / GKE for full control",
        "Define Models and Metrics so business users get consistent definitions across dashboards and AI queries",
        "Configure Metabot with the client's own LLM provider (Anthropic) for natural-language exploration",
        "Build operational and executive dashboards with email/Slack subscription delivery",
        "Set up row-level and column-level permissions for multi-team access",
        "Integrate dbt metadata via the community dbt-metabase package when the client is on dbt",
      ]}
    />
  </SectionWrapper>

  <SectionWrapper bg="white" py="lg">
    <WhenToChoose
      title="When Metabase is the right BI tool — and when it isn't"
      blocks={[
        {
          heading: 'Choose Metabase when:',
          bullets: [
            'You want self-service BI with a real AI assistant, at a reasonable price',
            'You want the option to self-host (Community Edition free, Pro self-host paid)',
            "You want Metabot AI features with BYO Anthropic key — available even in self-hosted",
            'Your team mixes technical and non-technical users',
          ],
        },
        {
          heading: 'Choose Looker instead when:',
          bullets: [
            'You need enterprise LookML governance and embedded analytics at scale',
            'Budget is 5k+/month and you are scaling across 50+ users',
          ],
        },
        {
          heading: 'Choose Lightdash instead when:',
          bullets: [
            "You're already on dbt and want metrics defined in code",
            'You want flat-rate pricing that does not scale with headcount',
          ],
        },
        {
          heading: 'Choose Steep instead when:',
          bullets: [
            'The team is entirely non-technical and you want the simplest metric-first UX',
            'Budget is under €500/month for a small team',
          ],
        },
      ]}
    />
  </SectionWrapper>
</TechnologyLayout>
